RACE.RACE_TEXT: HORSESHOE INDIANAPOLIS RACE 1 1M Dirt CR: 79. Maiden Special Weight Purse 34000. (PLUS UP TO 40% Indiana State Bred Supplement) FOR MAIDENS, FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD. Three Year Olds, 122 lbs.; Older, 125 lbs.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: HAPPY HELEN unhurried for the first half mile, closed ground to the far turn, started to circle four wide, instead dove back to the rail cutting the corner, tipped out at the head of the lane, engaged the leader in mid-stretch and out-dueled that one to the wire in a well managed ride. HEART HEADED WOMAN sent to the lead from the gates to open a clear advantage in the first turn, was well rated on a clear lead through the far turn, responded when engaged inside the eighth pole and just missed in a good effort. POOL NOODLE tracked the pacesetter from the rail in striking distance, loomed up on the turn when set to a drive and finished evenly for the show unable to sustain his rally. WICKED BEAUTIFUL slow early to trail the field into the far turn and rallied passed weakening rivals down the stretch. ABBREVIATION raced five wide in the first turn, settled to be mid-pack down the backside, failed to menace throughout and was vanned off after pulling up on the turn post-race. LIL CARRIE D prompted the pace for a half mile and faded on the far turn. KATERINA PETROVA stalked the pace from between horses into the final bend and flattened out.

ENTRY.NAME: Pool Noodle
ENTRY.COMMENT: tracked inside, early drive, loomed, evenly late

ENTRY.NAME: Happy Helen
ENTRY.COMMENT: unhurried early, steady gain, cut corner, tipped out, prevailed

ENTRY.NAME: Heart Headed Woman
ENTRY.OWNER: Dreamfields Inc and Little Flower LLC
ENTRY.COMMENT: sent, clear lead, well rated, responded, just missed, gamely

ENTRY.NAME: Abbreviation
ENTRY.COMMENT: 5 wide 1st turn, never menaced, vanned off

RACE.RACE_TEXT: HORSESHOE INDIANAPOLIS RACE 2 5 1/2F Dirt CR: 51. Maiden Claiming Purse 25000. (PLUS UP TO 40% Indiana State Bred Supplement) FOR MAIDENS, FILLIES TWO YEARS OLD. Weight, 121 lbs. Claiming Price $25,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: PAGEANT PURRFECT pressed the pace midway down the backstretch, bid two wide nearing the quarter pole to take command at the head of the lane, pulled clear down the lane and was unthreatened to the wire. CLASSIC MYSTERY broke a step tardy to be at the rear of the field, gained ground through the turn along the fence, angled four wide in upper stretch and found her best stride late to close with a rush. SAVE THE MOMENT stalked the leaders through the turn and finished well to be gaining down the lane. SUMMER DANCE set the pace on a clear lead to the turn, dueled with the winner through the turn to upper stretch and weakened late in the drive. VIVIS IN FRONT was prominently placed early on, dropped back in the turn and finished without impact. BLUESUP GREENSDOWN was never a factor.

ENTRY.COMMENT: step slow, rallied turn, angled clear, best stride late

ENTRY.OWNER: Hidden Creek Farm and Silva Racing LLC
ENTRY.COMMENT: pressed pace, took command, pulled clear

ENTRY.NAME: Summer Dance
ENTRY.COMMENT: set pace, dueled turn, weakened late

SLACKER set a pressured pace from the start, dueled through the turn on the lead and finished willingly to just hold the place. SAN RONIN reserved off the pace for half mile to be near the rear of the field, angled to the clear and made a good belated rally to just miss the place. HE SAID CASH tracked the pace from mid-pack and mounted a mild bid turning for home and finished evenly`. LITTLE RUSTY raced wide through the turn, drifted further out at the head of the lane, leveled out and rallied in the lane when switching leads. WE MISS OTIS reserved off the pace to the turn, made a brief bid turning for home and flattened out. PHILIP SNOW well placed for a half mile and faded coming home. WHITE SILVER SANDS flashed brief speed to duel on the early lead and tired in the turn.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: HORSESHOE INDIANAPOLIS RACE 4 5 1/2F Dirt CR: 66. Claiming Purse 13500. FOR REGISTERED INDIANA BREDS THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES. Three Year Olds, 122 lbs.; Older, 125 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race Since September 3 Allowed 2 lbs. Claiming Price $5,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: OVERTHETOPJUSTICE tracked the pace to the turn, ranged up three wide leaving the quarter pole, made a steady drive down the lane and prevailed in the final stride by a flared nostril. LEO'S ROAR broke alertly to be on top, settled just off the leader down the backside, moved to press the pace in the turn, dueled with the pacesetter to mid-stretch, shook clear of that one and was immediately engaged by the winner in deep stretch and was nailed in the final stride in a very game effort. MISTER MACHO sped to an early clear lead down the backstretch, came under pressure in the turn, dueled to midway down the lane and weakened deep in the drive. SUNSIGN unhurried for the first half mile, angled wide in upper stretch and made a late bid from five wide. MAS ORO stalked the leaders from between horses into the turn and failed to gain ground. RUNNING SMART prominently placed in striking distance for the first half mile and gave way down the lane. ALMIGHTYJUSTICE was never a factor.

ENTRY.COMMENT: ranged up 3w, determined drive, prevailed final stride

RACE.RACE_TEXT: HORSESHOE INDIANAPOLIS RACE 5 1M Turf CR: 66. Maiden Claiming Purse 32000. (PLUS UP TO 40% Indiana State Bred Supplement) FOR MAIDENS, TWO YEARS OLD. Weight, 122 lbs. Claiming Price $40,000. If this race is taken off the turf, it will be run at 1 mile and 70 yards on the main track.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: HAWKS CREEK unhurried in the early going to be in the back half of the field, avoided trouble in the first turn, gradually closed ground up the backside after working toward the rail, commenced a rally in the far turn angling out and bumping FULL DRESS BLUES, continued his bid four wide through the turn and closed determinedly down the lane to be up inside the final yards. COPPERLITE stalked the pace to the far turn, made a three wide bid turning for home, split rivals in the lane and finished willingly to be up for the place. HOT N LUCKY prompted the pace to the far turn, tipped out while rallying in the turn into the path of MITOLE'S BAYTOWN causing that one to nearly clip heels, rallied up to take the lead inside the final eight and was caught in deep stretch. EXTRA HALO broke alertly to set the pace, opened a clear lead in the final turn, kept on through the lane and was out-finished in deep stretch. INMYDREAMS raced four wide into the first turn, angled in bumping FULL DRESS BLUES, causing that one to crowd UKRAINE STRONG who took up sharply, then leveled off into a steady rhythm and went evenly failing to mount a bid. HOLD THE PHONE raced near the rear of the field to the head of the lane and passed weaker rivals in the stretch. FULL DRESS BLUES raced three wide into the first turn, was bumped by INMYDREAMS and pushed into UKRAINE STRONG, was gathered together and raced mid-pack down the backside, rallied up from three wide into the final bend, was bumped by HAWKS CREEK when that one angled out, took up to regain stride and finished evenly from there the victim of a very rough trip. MITOLE'S BAYTOWN stalked the pace from three wide to the far turn, nearly stumbled when cut-off by HOT N LUCKY and nearly lost his rider who maintained balance and gathered him up to finish evenly coming home. NO MANCHES was never a threat. UKRAINE STRONG raced just off the fence into the first turn when caused to check severely when INMYDREAMS angled inward, regained his momentum to be mid-pack down the backside and gradually faded having lost all chance early. LUCERITO BLANCO was never a factor. THE STEWARDS POSTED AN INQUIRY INTO THE ACTIONS OF HOT N LUCKY IN THE FAR TURN AND THE RIDER OF MITOLE'S BAYTOWN CLAIMED FOUL AGAINST HOT N LUCKY FOR THE INTERFERENCE ON THE TURN, IN ADDITION THE RIDER OF UKRAINE STRONG CLAIMED FOUL AGAINST INMYDREAMS FOR INTERFERENCE ON THE FIRST TURN, UPON REVIEW THE STEWARDS DISQUALIFIED HOT N LUCKY AND PLACED HIM SEVENTH AND DISQUALIFIED INMYDREAMS AND PLACED HIM TENTH. THE RACE WAS HAND TIMED DUE TO A TIMING MALFUNCTION.

ENTRY.COMMENT: broke alertly, set pace, cleared, outfinished late

ENTRY.COMMENT: unhurried early, bumped 2nd, angled 3w, closed well

ENTRY.NAME: dq-Inmydreams
ENTRY.COMMENT: angled in 1st turn, impeded rivals, evenly

RACE.RACE_TEXT: HORSESHOE INDIANAPOLIS RACE 7 1M Turf CR: 68. Maiden Special Weight Purse 34000. (PLUS UP TO 40% Indiana State Bred Supplement) FOR MAIDENS, TWO YEARS OLD. Weight, 122 lbs. If this race is taken off the turf, it will be run at 1 mile and 70 yards on the main track.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: MIGHTY KAI reserved off the early pace from two wide down the backside, circled five wide in the turn to commence a rally, drifted to the eight path in upper stretch and closed with a rush to be up in time. HEART OF OSCAR tracked the leaders from the fence through the turn, cut the corner and rallied well up the fence to just miss. FINN AND BRENNAN unhurried early to be near the rear turning for home and closed well through the lane in a good try the was not quite enough. NEW SPELL raced three wide through the first turn, made an early bid to loom up turning for home and finished evenly in the drive. MIDNIGHT AWARD rated in mid-pack through the far turn and failed to gain ground in the lane. BAYTOWN KITTY CAT set the pace comfortably to the quarter pole, responded when called upon for the drive and weakened late in the lane. NOBLE GENTLEMAN saved ground to be well positioned and continued on one-paced without a rally. LEMON MERINGUE prompted the pace for three quarters of a mile and gave way down the stretch. SHIESTY TO CHASE trailed through the first turn, made a mild move to the far turn and flattened out. BADGE OF WAR was never a factor. BARREL THIEF raced wide through the first turn to settle into mid-field down the backside and tired.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: HORSESHOE INDIANAPOLIS RACE 8 1M Turf CR: 94. Starter Optional Claiming Purse 26000. (PLUS UP TO 40% Indiana State Bred Supplement) FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE STARTED FOR A CLAIMING PRICE OF $10,000 OR LESS IN 2022 - 2023 OR CLAIMING PRICE $15,000. Three Year Olds, 120 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race At A Mile O r Over Since September 3 Allowed 2 lbs. Claiming Price $15,000 (Races Where Entered For $8,000 Or Less Not Considered In Estimating Allowances). If this race is taken off the turf, it will be run at 1 mile and 70 yards on the main track.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: NICHOLAS JONES settled in hand off the early pace, rallied through traffic on the turn to engage the leaders from four wide in mid-stretch and prevailed in the drive. GRACEFUL KITTEN tracked the leaders to the far turn, rallied up three wide to take a brief lead in upper stretch and was outkicked down the lane in a good effort. RIVER REDEMPTION reserved from the pace to be mid-pack, angled clear turning for home to threaten and finished willingly. MAJOR SPARKS unhurried early to be near the back of the field and made a steady gain down the lane to hit the board. ENGLISH CHALLENGE was slow early to be well off the leaders turning for home and mounted a belated rally down the lane finding his best stride late. INDOCUMENTADO tracked the leaders through the first turn, made an early bid splitting rivals down the backside and finished evenly unable to sustain his rally. COMMAND CENTRAL pressed the pace through the first turn, assumed command opening a clear advantage down the backside and weakened turning for home. GRAND HIDEAWAY showed brief speed taking the early lead and faded. CASANOVA KITTEN tracked the pacesetters down the backstretch, made a three wide bid in the turn to threaten and flattened out in the lane. GLOBAL EMPIRE was never a threat. DYNABLUE well placed in the first turn, dropped to the rear of the field on the backside and was never a factor.
